title: Immunotherapy of precancerous skin lesions may prevent squamous cell carcinoma

title_detail.value: Immunotherapy of precancerous skin lesions may prevent squamous cell carcinoma

summary: A treatment previously shown to clear the precancerous skin lesions called actinic keratosis now appears to reduce the chance that the treated skin will develop squamous cell carcinomas, the second most common form of skin cancer.
